abstract: The Senate on Tuesday voted to send to President Donald Trump an annual defense policy bill that combines a $738 billion Pentagon budget blueprint with legislation to provide federal employees with 12 weeks of paid parental leave.
snippet: The Senate on Tuesday voted to send to President Donald Trump an annual defense policy bill that combines a $738 billion Pentagon budget blueprint with legislation to provide federal employees with 12 weeks of paid parental leave.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Senate on Tuesday voted to send to President Donald Trump an annual defense policy bill that combines a $738 billion Pentagon budget blueprint with legislation to provide federal employees with 12 weeks of paid parental leave.
headline_main: Senate Sends Trump Defense Bill With Federal Parental Leave
headline_print_headline: Senate Sends Trump Defense Bill With Federal Parental Leave

abstract: The U.S. Senate voted overwhelmingly on Tuesday to pass a $738 billion defense policy bill that creates President Donald Trump's "Space Force" and gives federal employees 12 weeks of paid parental leave, sending it to the White House, where Trump has promised to quickly sign it into law.
snippet: The U.S. Senate voted overwhelmingly on Tuesday to pass a $738 billion defense policy bill that creates President Donald Trump's "Space Force" and gives federal employees 12 weeks of paid parental leave, sending it to the White House, where Trump ...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. Senate voted overwhelmingly on Tuesday to pass a $738 billion defense policy bill that creates President Donald Trump's "Space Force" and gives federal employees 12 weeks of paid parental leave, sending it to the White House, where Trump has promised to quickly sign it into law.
headline_main: Senate Sends Massive Defense Bill for Trump to Sign, Creating Space Force
headline_print_headline: Senate Sends Massive Defense Bill for Trump to Sign, Creating Space Force

abstract: Four of the current New York Times journalists who covered President Bill Clinton’s impeachment reminisce about that time and how it echoes in today’s coverage.
snippet: Four of the current New York Times journalists who covered President Bill Clinton’s impeachment reminisce about that time and how it echoes in today’s coverage.
lead_paragraph: Times Insider explains who we are and what we do, and delivers behind-the-scenes insights into how our journalism comes together.

abstract: The Trump administration on Tuesday refrained from endorsing a resolution passed by the U.S. Senate recognizing as a genocide the mass killings of Armenians a century ago, saying it continued to see them as "mass atrocities."
snippet: The Trump administration on Tuesday refrained from endorsing a resolution passed by the U.S. Senate recognizing as a genocide the mass killings of Armenians a century ago, saying it continued to see them as "mass atrocities."
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration on Tuesday refrained from endorsing a resolution passed by the U.S. Senate recognizing as a genocide the mass killings of Armenians a century ago, saying it continued to see them as "mass atrocities."
headline_main: Trump Administration Refrains From Endorsing U.S. Senate Measure on Armenian Genocide
headline_print_headline: Trump Administration Refrains From Endorsing U.S. Senate Measure on Armenian Genocide

abstract: Congress on Tuesday ratcheted up pressure on Syria, Russia and China while making it more difficult for the Trump administration to reduce commitments to allies from Europe to Asia.
snippet: Congress on Tuesday ratcheted up pressure on Syria, Russia and China while making it more difficult for the Trump administration to reduce commitments to allies from Europe to Asia.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Congress on Tuesday ratcheted up pressure on Syria, Russia and China while making it more difficult for the Trump administration to reduce commitments to allies from Europe to Asia.
headline_main: Congress Takes Aim at Syrian War Crimes, Russian Aggression
headline_print_headline: Congress Takes Aim at Syrian War Crimes, Russian Aggression

abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump plans to attend the annual Davos economic forum in January, a source familiar with the plan said on Tuesday.

abstract: A federal judge on Tuesday sentenced President Donald Trump's former deputy campaign chairman Rick Gates to 36 months of probation and ordered him to serve 45 days in jail, after he provided extensive cooperation that helped the government secure convictions for Republican operatives Roger Stone and Paul Manafort.
snippet: A federal judge on Tuesday sentenced President Donald Trump's former deputy campaign chairman Rick Gates to 36 months of probation and ordered him to serve 45 days in jail, after he provided extensive cooperation that helped the government secure ...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A federal judge on Tuesday sentenced President Donald Trump's former deputy campaign chairman Rick Gates to 36 months of probation and ordered him to serve 45 days in jail, after he provided extensive cooperation that helped the government secure convictions for Republican operatives Roger Stone and Paul Manafort.
headline_main: U.S. Judge Sentences Ex-Trump Campaign Deputy to Probation, 45 Days in Jail
headline_print_headline: U.S. Judge Sentences Ex-Trump Campaign Deputy to Probation, 45 Days in Jail

abstract: The end-of-year deal is the product of months of negotiations that fell short of both parties’ hopes.
snippet: The end-of-year deal is the product of months of negotiations that fell short of both parties’ hopes.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Brewers, distillers, racehorse owners, churches with parking lots and some wind energy producers won federal tax breaks in a last-hour congressional agreement on taxes and spending that was unveiled Tuesday morning.

abstract: Wisconsin's economic development agency needs to modify its procedures to ensure that tax credits aren't awarded for Foxconn Technology Group employees who don't perform work in the state, which would violate state law and the contract with the company, an audit released Tuesday said.
snippet: Wisconsin's economic development agency needs to modify its procedures to ensure that tax credits aren't awarded for Foxconn Technology Group employees who don't perform work in the state, which would violate state law and the contract with the co...
lead_paragraph: MADISON, Wis. — Wisconsin's economic development agency needs to modify its procedures to ensure that tax credits aren't awarded for Foxconn Technology Group employees who don't perform work in the state, which would violate state law and the contract with the company, an audit released Tuesday said.
headline_main: Audit Faults Plans to Credit Foxconn for Work Outside State
headline_print_headline: Audit Faults Plans to Credit Foxconn for Work Outside State

abstract: The U.S. House Ways and Means Committee approved a revised North American trade deal by voice vote on Tuesday, indicating likely broad support for implementing legislation in a House of Representatives floor vote on Thursday.
snippet: The U.S. House Ways and Means Committee approved a revised North American trade deal by voice vote on Tuesday, indicating likely broad support for implementing legislation in a House of Representatives floor vote on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. House Ways and Means Committee approved a revised North American trade deal by voice vote on Tuesday, indicating likely broad support for implementing legislation in a House of Representatives floor vote on Thursday.
headline_main: U.S. House Panel Advances North American Trade Deal, Sets Up Thursday House Vote
headline_print_headline: U.S. House Panel Advances North American Trade Deal, Sets Up Thursday House Vote
